- How would you generalize to 256-bit values with four halves?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to compare 128-bit values split across lanes and derive a scalar metric without 128-bit math.

## Key Concepts

- 128-bit data split into hi/lo lanes
- XOR to highlight differences
- 64-bit popcount for bit counting

## Code Example

```javascript
// Reference approach in C-like pseudocode; interview would use C/C++
int hammingDistance128(uint64_t a_hi, uint64_t a_lo, uint64_t b_hi, uint64_t b_lo) {
  uint64_t dh = a_hi ^ b_hi;
  uint64_t dl = a_lo ^ b_lo;
  return __builtin_popcountll(dh) + __builtin_popcountll(dl);
}
```

