## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to reason about multi-word bit manipulations and safe 64→128-bit extension without loops.

## Key Concepts
- 128-bit reversal via two 64-bit reversals and swapping halves
- Parallel-bits reversal (mask/shifts)
- Endianness-insensitive mapping of bit indices

## Code Example
```javascript
function reverse64(x) {
  x = (x >> 1n) & 0x5555555555555555n | (x & 0x5555555555555555n) << 1n;
  x = (x >> 2n) & 0x3333333333333333n | (x & 0x3333333333333333n) << 2n;
  x = (x >> 4n) & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fn | (x & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fn) << 4n;
  x = (x >> 8n) & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFn | (x & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFn) << 8n;
  x = (x >> 16n) & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFn | (x & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFn) << 16n;
  x = (x >> 32n) | (x << 32n);
  return x;
}
function reverse128(hi, lo) {
  const revLo = reverse64(lo);
  const revHi = reverse64(hi);
  return { hi: revLo, lo: revHi };
}
```

