```c
typedef struct { uint64_t hi; uint64_t lo; } uint128;

uint128 rotateLanesLeft128(uint128 x, unsigned n) {
    n &= 31;  // constrain n to valid range [0,31]
    uint32_t lo = (uint32_t)x.lo;
    uint32_t hi = (uint32_t)x.hi;
    uint32_t lo_r = (lo << n) | (lo >> (32 - n));
    uint32_t hi_r = (hi << n) | (hi >> (32 - n));
    return (uint128){.lo = lo_r, .hi = hi_r};
}
```

**Justification:** Each 32-bit lane rotates independently using the standard rotation identity `(x << n) | (x >> (32 - n))`. Masking `n` with 31 constrains it to the valid range [0,31].

**Tests:**
- `rotateLanesLeft128({0, 0x00000001}, 1)` returns `{0, 0x00000002}`
- `rotateLanesLeft128({0, 0x80000000}, 1)` returns `{0, 0x00000001}`

