questions.answer:
Use SWAR (SIMD Within A Register) to compute per-16-bit popcounts in parallel across both 64-bit halves, then pack the results into eight 16-bit lanes of the 128-bit result. This is achieved by reducing 64-bit values through pairwise, nibble, and byte popcount operations using only shifts and masks—no branches required.

```c
uint128 countBits128(uint128 x) {
    uint64_t lo = x.lo;
    uint64_t hi = x.hi;

    // Step 1: Pairwise popcount (each 2 bits -> count in 2 bits)
    lo = (lo & 0x5555555555555555) + ((lo >> 1) & 0x5555555555555555);
    hi = (hi & 0x5555555555555555) + ((hi >> 1) & 0x5555555555555555);

    // Step 2: Nibble popcount (each 4 bits -> count in 4 bits)
    lo = (lo & 0x3333333333333333) + ((lo >> 2) & 0x3333333333333333);
    hi = (hi & 0x3333333333333333) + ((hi >> 2) & 0x3333333333333333);

    // Step 3: Byte popcount (each 8 bits -> count in 8 bits)
    lo = (lo & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0F) + ((lo >> 4) & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0F);
    hi = (hi & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0F) + ((hi >> 4) & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0F);

    // Step 4: Horizontal add across bytes (16 bits each)
    lo = (lo & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF) + ((lo >> 8) & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF);
    hi = (hi & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF) + ((hi >> 8) & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF);

    // Step 5: Horizontal add across 16-bit lanes
    lo = (lo & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF) + ((lo >> 16) & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF);
    hi = (hi & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF) + ((hi >> 16) & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF);

    return (uint128){hi, lo};
}
```

**Justification**: The SWAR approach processes multiple 16-bit chunks simultaneously within each 64-bit register. Each reduction stage doubles the bit-width being counted while preserving per-lane results through carefully crafted masks. The final result contains eight 16-bit lanes, each holding the popcount of the corresponding 16-bit chunk of the input.

**Tests**:
```c
// Test 1: All zeros -> all lanes = 0
assert(countBits128((uint128){0, 0}).lo == 0);

// Test 2: Single bit set in each lane -> each lane = 1
uint128 t = {0x0001000100010001, 0x0001000100010001};
assert(countBits128(t).lo == 0x0001000100010001);
```

