reverseBitsInBytes128 reverses the bit order within each of the 16 bytes of a 128-bit value while preserving the overall byte order. It uses SWAR (SIMD Within A Register) bit manipulation masks applied in parallel to both the hi and lo 64-bit halves: first 0x55 (swap adjacent bits), then 0x33 (swap adjacent 2-bit pairs), then 0x0F (swap nibbles). Each mask is applied to all bytes simultaneously using a combination of AND, OR, and shift operations. The result is returned with the original hi/lo structure intact.

## Code Example
