**Approach:** Reverse bits within each 8-bit byte independently using a three-step parallel bit-twiddling technique. Each step swaps adjacent bit groups (nibbles, then 2-bit pairs, then individual bits) within every byte simultaneously.

```c
uint32 reverseBitsInEachByte32(uint32 x) {
  // Step 1: Swap adjacent nibbles (4-bit groups)
  x = ((x & 0xF0F0F0F0) >> 4) | ((x & 0x0F0F0F0F) << 4);
  // Step 2: Swap adjacent 2-bit pairs
  x = ((x & 0xCCCCCCCC) >> 2) | ((x & 0x33333333) << 2);
  // Step 3: Swap adjacent individual bits
  x = ((x & 0xAAAAAAAA) >> 1) | ((x & 0x55555555) << 1);
  return x;
}
```

**Justification:** This three-step algorithm reverses bits within each byte by progressively smaller groupings:
1. Nibble swap (4 bits): `0xF0` mask selects upper nibbles, `0x0F` selects lower
2. Bit-pair swap (2 bits): `0xCC` mask selects upper pairs, `0x33` selects lower  
3. Single-bit swap: `0xAA` mask selects even bits, `0x55` selects odd

The repeating mask patterns (`0xF0`, `0xCC`, `0xAA`) operate on all four bytes in parallel—no loops required.

**Quick Tests:**
- `0x00000001` → `0x00000080` (00000001 reversed within its byte becomes 10000000)
- `0x12345678` → `0x1C6A3C48` (each byte reversed independently)

