To compute parity branchlessly, reduce each 64-bit half to a single bit, then XOR the results together. For each half (hi and lo), repeatedly shift right and XOR to propagate the parity bit to the LSB:

```c
uint128 parity128(uint128 x) {
    uint64_t hi = (uint64_t)(x >> 64);
    uint64_t lo = (uint64_t)x;

    hi ^= hi >> 32; hi ^= hi >> 16; hi ^= hi >> 8; hi ^= hi >> 4;
    hi ^= hi >> 2; hi ^= hi >> 1;

    lo ^= lo >> 32; lo ^= lo >> 16; lo ^= lo >> 8; lo ^= lo >> 4;
    lo ^= lo >> 2; lo ^= lo >> 1;

    return (uint128)(hi ^ lo) & 1;
}
```

