SWAR-based popcount64 implementation using fixed-depth reduction. The algorithm processes bits in parallel through successive masking and addition stages:

```c
unsigned int popcount64(uint64_t x) {
    x = x - ((x >> 1) & 0x5555555555555555ULL);
    x = (x & 0x3333333333333333ULL) + ((x >> 2) & 0x3333333333333333ULL);
    x = (x + (x >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0FULL;
    x = x + (x >> 8);
    x = x + (x >> 16);
    x = x + (x >> 32);
    return x & 0xFF;
}
```

Edge cases: `popcount64(0) = 0` (no bits set), `popcount64(0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFULL) = 64` (all bits set).

